ight side of the bar.\nBut the timer also counts down automatically. So the game is a race against time, and I need to complete some task before the timer runs out.\nBut what is the task? I've been trying to figure this out for 124 actions.\nLet me look at the current image again. The blue rectangle is at cols 28-47 (approximately), rows 12-15. The charcoal/magenta blocks are at cols 36-39, rows 1-7. The yellow containers are at the bottom.\nWait, the game is over now. I need to restart or move to the next level. But the result says `game_over: true` and `run_complete: false`. This means the game ended but there might be more levels.\nActually, looking at the result more carefully, it says `level_completed: false` and `game_over: true`. This means I failed the level because the timer ran out.\nBut wait, the valid actions still include UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT, SPACE, and MOUSE. So maybe I can still interact with the game even though it's \"game over\"?\nLet me try clicking on the timer bar to reset it, or try pressing SPACE to restart the level.\nActually, let me first check if there's a way to restart the level. Maybe I need to click on a specific object or press a specific key.\nLet me try pressing SPACE to see if it restarts the level.", "kind": "reasoning", "inContext": false}, {"label": "TOOL CALL: python", "content": "<tool_call>\n<function=python>\n<parameter=code>\n# Try pressing SPACE to restart after game over\naction(['SPACE'])\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "TOOL RESULT: python", "content": "executed: true\naction_num: 125\nlevel: 1\nscore: 0\nreward: 0.0\nstate: NOT_FINISHED\nvalid_actions:\n  - UP\n  - DOWN\n  - LEFT\n  - RIGHT\n  - SPACE\n  - MOUSE\nboard_changed: true\ndone: false\nlevel_completed: false\ngame_over: false\nrun_complete: false\naction_display: SPACE\nexecuted_actions:\n  - SPACE\nrun_elapsed_seconds: 5164.244978332\ntime_remaining_seconds: 2755.755021668", "kind": "tool", "inConte